commentBody:
@Liz
Same with the ‘log’ in my opinion. I made it one year and it was lovely. It received praise, and that was enough.😊 
I am, however, excited enough about these small treats to put the time and I think

Instead of "cutting-in" the butter into the flour...  do this:
  --partially freeze the unsalted butter;
  --also freeze a grater that has larger rather than smaller holes;
  --grate some butter into the flour and then mix within the flour;
  --do this repeatedly until all butter has been turned into the flour.

This gives just the "gravel" texture you want, but it is much easier!
